channel.title: Why cant i compile? problem inside this
channel.description: [color=red][size=10pt][b]Okay, thanks for coming to read this and hope you could help :) alright.. problem is when i click 'compile' on my source files it Almost always comes up saying somthing like, you do not have the right java or you dont have java or you dont have jdk 5.0 or 6.0 when i have jdk 6 update 10... soo im just confused cause this hapens on every source i choose. if anyone could help i would be very happy and may give you a staff position on my server :) thank you[/b].[/[/size][/size]color]

item.title: Why cant i compile? problem inside this
item.dc:creator: @Green020395 Green020395
item.description:
@Green020395 wrote:

Go to compile.bat right click, and edit it, make sure the File Name and location URL MATCH. If not then the compiler won’t work. In other words, open up your java folder, look at the top where it shows the location URL then see if it matches what it saved.
